By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – The Nigeria Communication Commission (NCC) has reacted to the rumour making rounds linking 5G to COVID-19, and has cleared all doubts surrounding the conspiracy theory. The statement from NCC reads: “In view of the recent development in which misleading materials with no proven evidence being circulated to link CORONAVIRUS or COVID-19 with 5G Technology, it has become imperative for the Nigerian Communications Commission (NCC) to provide the following clarifications;Firstly, there is no correlation between 5G Technology and COVID-19. 5G is an advancement on today’s 4G technology designed to transform the world positively.Secondly, there is no deployment of 5G in Nigeria at th moment. The NCC back in November 2019 approved trial test for 5G for a period of three (3) months and th the trial has been concluded and installation decommissioned.The trial among others was to study and observe any health or security challenges the 5G network might present. Relevant stakeholders including members of t security agencies were invited to participate during the trial.The NCC will continue to maintain its policy of technology neutrality and will continue to encourage Service providers to deploy the best technology that wil meet the needs of the society in a secured and friendly manner.The following are some Frequently Asked Questions :